title: Grateful Dead Live at The Tower Theatre on 1976-06-24
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, Big River, Friend Of The Devil, Cassidy, It Must Have Been The Roses, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain, Scarlet Begonias, Promised Land

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Samson & Delilah, Wharf Rat-> Dancin' In The Streets-> Sugar Magnolia

reviews.review_text:
Just plain awesome.... Awesome recording, awesome performance, and kudos for the fine work done on this.
And to think, this or one of the others in this 1976 Tower run could have been my first GD concert. But, not really having anyone to go with, I passed on the mail-in ticket option and didn't see my first show until the following April.
The tower 76' Set 1 contains a real nice FOTD.Set 2 is smokin with a sweet HSF.Definitely worth a listen.
